Steps to follow in case of system wash out

1 go to softwares&updates in settings and select india in the download from option

2 do an update

sudo apt-get update

3 when everythings fine and updated install pip

install the following first to install pip

sudo apt-get install python-setuptools python2.7-dev build-essential
//build-essential might throw some error have to update requirements for build essential

4 install pip

sudo easy_install pip

5 install virtual environment wrapper

pip install virtualenvwrapper

6 create a virtual environment

mkvirtualenv 'name'

install required python packages in the virtualenv

7 install chrome 

8 install screen ruler from software center

9 install pycharm 

//enter bin inside the pycharm folder
cd bin

//run pycharm shell to install the same.
. pycharm.sh

10 install git 

sudo apt-get install git

//config git
git config --global user.name "ashwin"
git config --global user.email "ashwin@themode.net"

11 install postgres

//Access root by running the following command:

sudo su -

//To install PostgreSQL, as well as the necessary server software, run the following command:

apt-get install postgresql postgresql-contrib

//Configure PostgreSQL to start up upon server boot.

update-rc.d postgresql enable

//Start PostgreSQL.

service postgresql start

12 install redis

sudo apt-get -y install redis-server
